>I have a textbook coming out in late spring/early summer from Macmillan, 
>entitled "Network and Internetwork Security", which will cover the following:
>
>Chapter 1: Overview
>PART I INTERNETWORK SECURITY PRINCIPLES
>Chapter 2: Conventional Encryption
>Chapter 3: Confidentiality Using Conventional Encryption
>Chapter 4: Public-Key Cryptography
>Chapter 5: Authentication and Digital Signatures
>Chapter 6: Intruders, Viruses, and Worms
>PART II INTERNETWORK SECURITY PRACTICE
>Chapter 7: Cryptographic Algorithms
>Chapter 8: Authentication and Key Exchange
>Chapter 9: Electronic Mail Privacy
>Chapter 10: Network Management Security
>
>The book covers topics recommended in ACM and IEEE curricula guidelines 
>and includes homework problems, guides to further reading, glossary, etc.

Congratulations.  I look forward to seeing it.  If it works as a text book,
it will probably do very well.

